name: Tangela
flavorText: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.
Attack1Text: Heal 40 damage from each of your Grass Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Hoppip
flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Skiploom
flavorText: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of your remaining Prize cards.

name: Yanma
flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Ability1Text: If you have exactly 4 cards in your hand, ignore all Energy in the attack cost of each of this Pokemon's attacks.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Yanmega BREAK
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Seedot
flavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, if this Pokemon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's next turn, it is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP becomes 10 instead.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokemon if that damage is 60 or less.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.
Attack1Text: Until the end of your opponent's next turn, each Stadium or Pokemon Tool card in play has no effect. (This includes cards that come into play on that turn.)
Attack2Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Foongus
flavorText: It lures Pokemon with its pattern that looks just like a Poke Ball then releases poison spores.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may put 3 Poke Ball cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poke Balls, in a swaying motion.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Confused, it is now Paralyzed.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.
Attack1Text: Put 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Chimchar
flavorText: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Monferno
flavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

name: Infernape
flavorText: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If you have fewer than 10 Fire Energy cards in your discard pile, this attack does nothing. Shuffle 10 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Talonflame BREAK
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Litleo
flavorText: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokemon are quick to fight.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tool cards attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Pyroar BREAK
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokemon. Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to each of those Pokemon.

name: Volcanion-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Fire Energy card from your hand. If you do, during this turn, your Basic Fire Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Mantine
flavorText: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.
Attack1Text: Discard as many cards as you like from your hand. Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 90 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Shellos
flavorText: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

name: Gastrodon
flavorText: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless more, and its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavorText: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Samurott
flavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Attack1Text: If the damage from this attack reduces your opponent's Active Pokemon's HP to 60 or less, that Pokemon is Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Clauncher
flavorText: Through controlled expulsions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Clawitzer
flavorText: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Special Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Mega Evolution Pokemon.

name: Clawitzer BREAK
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn. During your next turn, any damage done to that Pokemon by attacks is increased by 120 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bergmite
flavorText: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Avalugg
flavorText: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back make it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck. For each Water Energy card you discarded in this way, discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Mareep
flavorText: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ampharos
flavorText: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon-EX.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Joltik
flavorText: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokemon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. Also apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for Nidoran ♀ and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: An aggressive Pokemon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.
Attack2Text: If Nidorina is on your Bench, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
Ability1Text: Your Nidoqueen's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Evolution Pokemon on your Bench.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: These Pokemon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.
Attack1Text: Move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokemon to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon. Put 8 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Litwick
flavorText: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokemon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and discard them. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Lampent
flavorText: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.
Attack1Text: Each player either draws or discards cards until that player has 4 cards in his or her hand. (Your opponent does this first.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Discard the other card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Supporter card in your discard pile.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Portal Strike during your next turn.

name: Mankey
flavorText: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Flop attack's base damage is 50.

name: Primeape
flavorText: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If, before doing damage, your opponent's Active Pokemon has more remaining HP than this Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Probopass
flavorText: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Anorith
flavorText: A Pokemon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.
Ability1Text: Each of your Restored Pokemon has no Weakness.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Armaldo
flavorText: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon to 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is Poisoned, put 3 more damage counters on that Pokemon between turns. This effect can be applied more than once.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Poisoned Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Weavile
flavorText: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Pokemon Tool card attached to 1 of your Pokemon into your hand.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Move as many damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon as you like to any of your opponent's other Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage times the number of your Pawniard.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
Attack1Text: Attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Yveltal BREAK
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Steelix-EX
Attack1Text: You may do 50 more damage. If you do, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 100 damage times the number of heads.

name: M Steelix-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Shieldon
flavorText: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bastiodon
flavorText: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokemon that feeds on grass and berries.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon equal to the damage done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Klang
flavorText: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Klinklang
flavorText: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.
Ability1Text: Any damage done to this Pokemon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Gear Spinner attack does 70 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cobalion
flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Basic Pokemon during your opponent's next turn. This Pokemon can't use Quick Guard during your next turn.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Magearna-EX
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to each of your Pokemon that has any Metal Energy attached to it. (Existing effects are not removed.)
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Soul Blaster attack's base damage is 60.

name: Marill
flavorText: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Azumarill
flavorText: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it's in the water.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Gardevoir-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached to them, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: M Gardevoir-EX
Attack1Text: Discard as many of your Benched Pokemon as you like. This attack does 10 more damage for each Benched Pokemon you discarded in this way.

name: Klefki
flavorText: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may discard all cards attached to this Pokemon and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon as a Pokemon Tool card. Prevent any damage done to the Pokemon this card is attached to by attacks from your opponent's Mega Evolution Pokemon. If this card is attached to a Pokemon, discard this card at the end of your opponent's turn.

name: Xerneas
flavorText: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokemon. For each of those Pokemon, search your deck for a Fairy Energy card and attach it to that Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Xerneas BREAK
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has any Pokemon BREAK in play, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Deino
flavorText: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Hydreigon
flavorText: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokemon devours everything in its path!
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 40 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard as many Darkness Energy attached to your Pokemon as you like. This attack does 50 damage times the amount of Darkness Energy you discarded in this way.

name: Hydreigon BREAK
Attack1Text: Discard 3 Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Meowth
flavorText: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only on your first turn. Discard an Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Persian
flavorText: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon evolved from Meowth during this turn, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Aipom
flavorText: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Ambipom
flavorText: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck. If that card is an Energy card, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Rufflet
flavorText: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Braviary
flavorText: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack does 120 damage minus 20 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Fletchling
flavorText: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in your hand when you are setting up to play, you may put it face down as your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Volcanion-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Fire Energy card from your hand. If you do, during this turn, your Basic Fire Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Steelix-EX
Attack1Text: You may do 50 more damage. If you do, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 100 damage times the number of heads.

name: M Steelix-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Magearna-EX
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to each of your Pokemon that has any Metal Energy attached to it. (Existing effects are not removed.)
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Soul Blaster attack's base damage is 60.

name: Gardevoir-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached to them, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: M Gardevoir-EX
Attack1Text: Discard as many of your Benched Pokemon as you like. This attack does 10 more damage for each Benched Pokemon you discarded in this way.

name: Volcanion-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Fire Energy card from your hand. If you do, during this turn, your Basic Fire Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Gardevoir-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon and your opponent's Active Pokemon have the same amount of Energy attached to them, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.
